cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about incorporating syntactic information into text modeling using variational autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new method for representation learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of probabilistic models also suggests a connection to neural networks and statistical learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions experiments with generating examples, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) if the generated examples are images.
